The paper deals with a tool that helps novice programmers with fixing buggy commands, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also introduces a language called FixIt, which can be considered a programming language (cs.PL). The algorithm used for synthesizing FixIt rules is based on lazy VSA, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the tool involves benchmark problems, which can be considered a form of experimentation and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with improving the usability of command-line tools, which can be considered a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
